<p><strong>Author</strong>: A.A. Scitovsky, M. Cline, P.R. Lee  		<strong>Title</strong>: Medical Costs of Patients with AIDS in San  		Francisco <strong>Source, date</strong>: <b><i>JAMA</i></b> 1986  		256(22):3103-3106 <strong>Categories</strong>: cost, health care financing  		<strong>Location/Population</strong>: adult, San Francisco</p>
<p><strong>Summary</strong>:</p>
<p>Group calculates direct inpatient care for adult gay men in San  		Francisco General Hospital to be $27,571 from diagnosis to death (224 days on  		average). Number of hospital admissions, 3.2, days in hospital per admission  		was 34.7</p>
<p><strong>Issues/Recommendations</strong>:</p>
<p>Estimates for direct cost for children can be expected to be higher, as  		children live longer, and stay in the hospital longer.</p>
