<p><strong>Author</strong>: P. Thomas, H. Jaffe, et. al.  		<strong>Title</strong>: Unexplained Immunodeficiency in Children  		<strong>Source, date</strong>: <b><i>JAMA</i></b> 1984, 252:639-644  		<strong>Categories</strong>: public health; natural history  		<strong>Location/Population</strong>: children</p>
<p><strong>Summary</strong>:</p>
<p>This was one of the first publications linking AIDS to infants. The data  		is limited because it was before testing was available for AIDS antibody. The  		key finding is that a high proportion of infants were premature--38%  		(10/26).</p>
<p><strong>Issues/Recommendations</strong>:</p>
<p>38 percent of AIDS infants were premature--added burden on the Public  		Health System.</p>
